## Routed Findings driving Sprint 3 Phase 2b
- FIND-013 (route 2b) — ParsedNote.body retained as `string`; verification-architecture
  port contract requires `Body` VO. Sprint 3 Red captured this as 2 type-check errors
  at step2-scan-vault.test.ts:92 (_BodyIsBody) and :105 (_BodyTypeMatchesPort).

## Phase 2b Implementation (minimum code to turn 2 type-check errors green)
- promptnotes/src/lib/domain/app-startup/stages.ts:
  - Added `Body` to the imports from `promptnotes-domain-types/shared/value-objects`.
  - Tightened `ParsedNote.body` from `string` to `Body` (Brand<string, "Body">).
  - Updated docstring to explicitly cite FIND-005 + FIND-013 and the Tier-0 contract
    that the parser port owns Body VO construction; scanVault never re-wraps raw strings.
- promptnotes/src/lib/domain/app-startup/scan-vault.ts:
  - Removed the residual `parsed.body as unknown as Body` cast at the snapshot construction
    site (formerly line 127). `parsed.body` already has type `Body` after the stages.ts
    tightening, so the cast becomes both unnecessary and contractually wrong (it would
    bypass the boundary the verification-architecture port catalog assigns to the parser).
  - Removed the now-unused `Body` import.

## Cascading Test Stub Updates (mechanical, no behavior change)
- step2-scan-vault.test.ts: introduced `makeBody(raw: string): Body` helper next to the
